# Process Images to Jekyll (Rule)

When working in this repository, follow these guidelines whenever the user:
- Attaches one or more images and
- Mentions processing them into blog posts, Jekyll posts, or bilingual (Chinese/English) content.

## Behavior

- Prefer to follow the detailed steps defined in the workflow file:
  - `.agents/workflows/process_images_to_jekyll_cursor.md`
- Treat that workflow as the source of truth for:
  - How to inspect and crop images so that only the kung fu moves/techniques are kept, and save those cropped regions under `assets/images/blogs/` as `.png`
  - How to extract Chinese text and visual descriptions
  - How to structure the Chinese and English Jekyll posts (frontmatter, body, images)

## How to respond

When the user attaches images and asks to process them (or similar wording):
1. Explicitly note that you are following the **“Process Images to Jekyll (Cursor Workflow)”** in `.agents/workflows/process_images_to_jekyll_cursor.md`.
2. Execute the steps from that workflow against the attached images.
3. At the end, summarize:
   - Paths of the generated Chinese and English posts
   - Paths and filenames of any cropped images created in `assets/images/blogs/`
   - Any key assumptions you made (e.g., chosen slugs, directories).

